  "prompt": "Is a 4G LTE a 4G phone?",
  "response": "Yes, a 4G LTE phone is considered a 4G phone. LTE stands for Long-Term Evolution, and it is a standard for wireless communication of high-speed data for mobile phones and data terminals. It significantly improves internet speeds and overall performance compared to previous generations. So, when you have a 4G LTE phone, you are using a device that supports the fourth generation (4G) mobile network technology.",
